Vice President Mike Pence visited Cornerstone Ministries Church in Murrysville, Pennsylvania to express his gratitude to the Women's Choice Network and other pro-life organizations. He commended their efforts in supporting young women and saving the lives of babies. Pence also highlighted the role of crisis pregnancy centers in promoting the sanctity of life and thanked Judge Cheryl Allen for her pro-life advocacy. He emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting the right to life and pledged continued support for these organizations.